wiki.content: “BIRDS OF A FEATHER” is one of the standout tracks from Billie Eilish’s third album HIT ME HARD AND SOFT. The second single became a massive success, gaining widespread acclaim for its emotional depth and resonating with a global audience. It eventually became Billie Eilish’s first song to top the Billboard Global 200 chart, especially after her performance during the 2024 Summer Olympics closing ceremony. Thematically, the song delves into the longing for deep love and lasting connection, exploring the idea of kindred spirits finding one another. The track is known for its emotive lyrics and Billie’s impassioned vocal delivery, making it one of the most heartfelt and memorable pieces from the album. Musically, “BIRDS OF A FEATHER” features a powerful blend of impactful songwriting and rich production. It has been praised for its ability to evoke strong emotional reactions, largely due to Billie’s ability to connect deeply with her audience through her lyrics and voice. Read more on Last.fm.
